		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Memex</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="dablink">For the Software Company, see <a href="/wiki/Memex_Technology_Limited" title="Memex Technology Limited">Memex Technology Limited</a>.</div>
<p>The <b>memex</b> (a <a href="/wiki/Portmanteau" title="Portmanteau">portmanteau</a> of "memory extender"<sup class="noprint Template-Fact"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources&#160;since December 2008" style="white-space: nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed">citation needed</a></i>]</span></sup>) is the name given by <a href="/wiki/Vannevar_Bush" title="Vannevar Bush">Vannevar Bush</a> to the theoretical proto-<a href="/wiki/Hypertext" title="Hypertext">hypertext</a> computer system he proposed in his 1945 <i><a href="/wiki/The_Atlantic_Monthly" title="The Atlantic Monthly" class="mw-redirect">The Atlantic Monthly</a></i> article <i><a href="/wiki/As_We_May_Think" title="As We May Think">As We May Think</a></i>. The memex has influenced the development of subsequential <a href="/wiki/Hypertext" title="Hypertext">hypertext</a> and intellect augmenting computer systems.</p>
